WorkItem.Description:
Rating Control (Input.Toolkit) InvalidCastException in Blend.
 
Hi my Layouter Colleague found a bug in the Rating control, when he wanted to style the Rating control.
to Reproduce
Make a simple WPF App.
Put a Rating control on a window.
In Blend create a style (copy) on the Rating control.
then go to properties of the rating control
 on the style property try to edit the style and the exception occurs:

System.InvalidCastException ist aufgetreten.
  Message="Das Objekt des Typs \"System.String\" kann nicht in Typ \"System.Windows.Controls.RatingItem\" umgewandelt werden."
  Source="System.Core"
  StackTrace:
       bei System.Linq.Enumerable.<CastIterator>d__aa`1.MoveNext()
       bei System.Collections.Generic.List`1..ctor(IEnumerable`1 collection)
       bei System.Linq.Enumerable.ToList[TSource](IEnumerable`1 source)
       bei System.Windows.Controls.Rating.UpdateValues() in C:\Test\WPFToolKit\wpf-40156\Toolkit-development\Input\Rating\System\Windows\Controls\Rating.cs:Zeile 481.
  InnerException: 

 for us i did a workaround for designmode:

      protected override void OnItemsChanged(NotifyCollectionChangedEventArgs e)
        {
            EventHandler layoutUpdated = null;
            layoutUpdated =
                delegate
                {
                    this.LayoutUpdated -= layoutUpdated;
                  if ( System.Diagnostics.Process.GetCurrentProcess().ProcessName.ToLowerInvariant() != "blend")
                  {
                    UpdateValues();
                    UpdateDisplayValues();
                  }
                };
            this.LayoutUpdated += layoutUpdated;
 
            this.ItemCount = this.Items.Count;
 
            base.OnItemsChanged(e);
        }

Maybe you have a better fix for this, and it will be soon fixed in a next version.
 
Thanks
 
Patrick
